revision.text:
{{DISPLAYTITLE:Ceiling_LowerToHighestFloor}} {{Special|192|tag, speed|Ceiling|LowerToHighestFloor}}
* ''tag'': Tag of affected sector * ''speed'': How quickly the ceiling moves
==Usage==
Lowers a ceiling to the height of the highest floor sorrounding it. If the ceiling is at a position lower than the highest floor, it will instantly rise to the level of the highest floor. If ''tag'' is 0, then the sector on the line's back side is used.
==Examples== {{noexamples}}
